 beautiful castle of Hikone, which still stands. His descendant Ii Naosuke (1815–1860) ruled Japan for two years as Tairō (Great Elder) and played a major part in signing treaties that opened Japan to foreign trade at the end of the Tokugawa Shōgunate. He was assassinated by adherents of the anti-foreign party."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Judicael de Malestroit II was born in 1135, in Malestroit, Morbihan, Brittany, France as the son of Payen de Malestroit I. He had at least 1 son with Jeanne de LARGOËT. He died in France."},"et":{"1135–":"1135–Surnud","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1180–1229":"1180–1229","1110–1135":"1110–1135","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","ABT 1180":"umbes 1180","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","1229":"1229","MALESTROIT":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa",", , , France":"Prantsusmaa","Malestroit, Vannes, Morbihan, Bretagne, France":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1135–":"1135–Kuollut","1135–Male":"1135–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1180–1229":"1180–1229","1110–1135":"1110–1135","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","ABT 1180":"noin 1180","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","1229":"1229","MALESTROIT":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, Ranska",", , , France":"Ranska","Malestroit, Vannes, Morbihan, Bretagne, France":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, Ranska"},"fr":{"1135–":"1135–Décédé","1135–Male":"1135–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1180–1229":"1180–1229","1110–1135":"1110–1135","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","ABT 1180":"environ 1180","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","1229":"1229","MALESTROIT":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, France",", , , France":"France","Malestroit, Vannes, Morbihan, Bretagne, France":"Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, France","lifeSummary":"Judicael de Malestroit II est né en 1135, à Malestroit, Morbihan, Bretagne, France, fils de Payen de Malestroit I. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Jeanne de LARGOËT. Il est décédé à France."},"de